text: On the execute tab, the list of subtasks for an epic should be sorted by status in this order: In Progress, In Review, Ready, Backlog, Done

proposedTasks.title: Sort epic subtasks by status priority in Execute tab
proposedTasks.description: In the Execute tab's epic card task list, sort child tasks by status in a fixed display order: In Progress  In Review  Ready  Backlog  Done. Within each status group, preserve the existing sort order (priority then creation order). Acceptance criteria: (1) Tasks in the epic card's collapsible table are grouped by status in the specified order. (2) A task that transitions status (e.g., Ready  In Progress) moves to the correct position on the next render/update. (3) Within the same status group, tasks remain sorted by beads priority (0 highest) then by ID as tiebreaker. (4) Done tasks appear last so active work is always visible without scrolling.

taskTitles: Sort epic subtasks by status priority in Execute tab
